definition.value: An unsymmetrical C3 cyanine dye having 1,3-benzoxazol-2-yl and quinolinium-4-yl substituents.
A fluorescent dye having an absorption wavelength of 530 nm and an emission wavelength of 550 nm, derived from fluorescein.
A group derived from indole by removal of a hydrogen atom from a ring atom.
Any compound containing two aryl groups connected by a single C atom.
A group derived from indolin-2-one by removal of a hydrogen atom from a ring atom.
Monocyclic compounds containing a diazirine ring.

A phosphinate ester-containing N-acyl derivative of (4S)-cyclohexyl-L-proline. It is used for the treatment of hypertension and heart failure. A pro-drug, it is hydrolysed in vivo to the corresponding phosphininc acid, fosinoprilat, which is the active metabolite.
A group derived from pyridine by removal of a hydrogen atom from a ring carbon atom.
Members of the class of boronate ester that include compounds containing a five-membered ring boronic ester.
An X-rhodamine compound having a carboxy substituent at the 5-position.
An X-rhodamine triethylammonium salt having a carboxy substituent at the 5-position.

The sodium salt of fosinopril. It is used for the treatment of hypertension and heart failure. A pro-drug, its phosphinate ester group is hydrolysed in vivo to give the corresponding phosphininc acid, fosinoprilat, which is the active metabolite.
A group derived from pyrrole by removal of a hydrogen atom.
Compounds containing two phosphane groups linked directly by a P-P bond or via a hydrocarbon bridge.
An organosulfur heterocyclic compound containing a six-member aliphatic saturated heterocycle made up of two sulfur atoms and four carbon atoms.
